<Link id="l01151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1151"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Some instructions that produce vectors have semantics that make it more</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1152"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// difficult to determine whether the VL can be reduced. For example, some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1153"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions, such as reductions, may write lanes past VL to a scalar</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1154"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// register. Other instructions, such as some loads or stores, may write</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1155"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// lower lanes using data from higher lanes. There may be other complex</span></CodeLine>
